    "120792954": {
      "title": "Self-similar solidification of an alloy from a cooled boundary",
      "abstract": "The self-similar solidification process of an alloy from a cooled boundary is studied on the basis of two models with a planar front and mushy layer. Approximate and exact analytical solutions of the process, which demonstrate unusual dynamics near the point of constitutional supercooling, are found. The rate of solidification and front position of the solid/mush boundary (parabolic growth rate constant) are expressed in an explicit form in the case of slow dynamics of this boundary. The theory under consideration is in a good agreement with experimental and numerical studies carried out by Huppert and Worster for ice growing from aqueous salt solutions."
    },
    "56009618": {
      "title": "Solidification of an alloy from a cooled boundary",
      "abstract": "On presente un modele mathematique pour la region de croissance dendritique ou cellulaire qui se forme souvent pendant la solidification des alliages. Ce modele traite la region mixte (solide et liquide) comme un continuum dont les proprietes varient avec la fraction volumique locale du solide. On suppose que les transports de chaleur et de solute se font par diffusion, le modele est ferme par une condition d'equilibre aux limites. Resultats pour la solidification dirigee d'un alliage a partir d'une paroi plane"
    }
